[^TEXT: KING CHARLS HIS TRYAL AT THE HIGH COURT OF JUSTICE SITTING IN
WESTMINSTER HALL: BEGUN ON SATURDAY, JAN. 20. ENDED JAN. 27. 1648. 
ALSO, HIS MAJESTIES SPEECH ON THE SCAFFOLD, IMMEDIATELY BEFORE HIS 
EXECUTION, ON TUESDAY, IAN. 30. TOGETHER WITH THE SEVERAL SPEECHES OF 
DUKE HAMILTON, THE EARL OF HOLLAND, AND THE LORD CAPEL, IMMEDIATELY 
BEFORE THEIR EXECUTION, ON FRIDAY, MARCH 9. 1649.
THE SECOND EDITION, MUCH ENLARGED, AND FAITHFULLY CORRECTED.
LONDON, PRINTED BY J. M. FOR PETER COLE, FRANCIS TYTON, AND JOHN 
PLAYFORD. 
1650.
